---
const stack = [
  "Figma",
  "Framer",
  "Webflow",
  "Cursor",
  "Linear",
  "Notion",
  "After Effects",
  "Principle",
];
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32 bg-[color:var(--color-ink)] text-[color:var(--color-paper)]">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1280px] grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
    <div class="md:col-span-4 reveal">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-4">About</div>
      <h2 class="serif text-5xl md:text-6xl">A designer, first.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6 space-y-6 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/80 reveal">
      <p>
        I started in print, fell into product, and never looked back. Today I lead
        design for early-stage teams that care as much about how a thing
        <em>feels</em> as how it works — and I write code well enough to keep
        engineers honest.
      </p>
      <p>
        My work tends to be quiet on the surface and loud underneath: clean
        interfaces, sharp typography, opinionated systems, and a lot of cut
        features. The best design decisions are the ones nobody notices.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work I sketch architecture, brew unreasonable amounts of
        coffee, and occasionally write about the craft of design.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-white/15">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-4">Toolkit</div>
        <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {stack.map((t) => (
            <li class="text-sm border border-white/20 rounded-full px-3 py-1">{t}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
